{"ALLY":[{"def":"To unite, or form a connection between, as between families by marriage, or between princes and states by treaty, league, or confederacy; -- often followed by to or with.","pos":""},{"def":"To connect or form a relation between by similitude, resemblance, friendship, or love.","pos":""}],"ALLYL":[{"def":"An organic radical, C3H5, existing especially in oils of garlic and mustard.","pos":""}],"ALLYLENE":[{"def":"A gaseous hydrocarbon, C3H4, homologous with acetylene; propine.","pos":""}]}